@node SysopMenuInfo "SysopMenu - the TransAmiga Sysop Menu"

TA-SMS is a highly configurable Sysop Menu for TransAmiga BBS,
the only real Shareware BBS System available for the Amiga. 
TA-SMS is different from the others, because it has some
really remarkable @{" features " link features}.
@endnode

@node "Introduction"
Introduction

Welcome to TA-SMS, a different Sysopmenu program for @{" TransAmiga BBS " link TransAmiga } 
systems. There was only one SysopMenu I knew (TrMaint), but I didn't quite like it. 
I wanted something different with more possebilities. The program is fully functionable,
and most ideas are implemented, but more ideas are coming soon in newer versions.

Since I received a couple of responses (e.g. thanks, it's wonderful), 
I've been expanding the program. 
Lots of testing etc. But most of all, I use it!

@endnode

@node "Features"
List of Features 

When I programmed the TA-SMS  more and more ideas came to me...
So that's the result of my work.

-all functions, that TrMaint has !
-the CoSysop (if exists) can't edit or delete the Sysop, can't edit himself
-if he read the logs, he can't read any Passwords from users.
-all activities from the CoSys are shown in the logfile
-show the CoSys the meaning of flags, so he could work much better
-in useredit, only the Sysop can read and edit Passwords from users
-the CoSys can't give more access to users, as the Sysop wants.
-verbose userlisting supported editing and continueing from last userposition
-it's possible to update fileareas from the SysopMenu
-it's possible to rescan message areas
-it's possible to edit the Newstext (local and online)
-one config for each line makes it high configurable
-you can use your prefered commands and say on which access it will be executeable
-it's full multilanguage (uses the same as the user uses in TransAmiga if exist)

@endnode

@node Installation "Installing SysopMenu"
Installing TransAmiga-Sysop Manipulation System

The following commands must exists and in your Dos path:
-Trufl
-TrShell
-TrAL
-TAEd (Sami Radwan's TransAmiga-Editor)
-Arexx V1.15
-TransAmiga V1.12g2 or newer

-FIFO must be installed! (cause TrShell)

It's quite simple. Since SMS v2.0 simple start the SMS.install script.

   @{"Install SMS v2.02" SYSTEM "Installer Install-SMS APPNAME SMS MINUSER EXPERT LANGUAGE english NOPRETEND NOLOG NOPRINTER"}

@endnode

@node configfile "The configfile"
The SMS_#.cfg configfile and what it means

Secret			<- The Password to enter the SysopMenu
BBS:extras/SysopM/      <- Path to all SysopMenu files ':' or '/' is necessary
News			<- Name of the News File (including the path)
100			<- MaxAccess a CoSys can give other users
Ed -sticky	        <- Name of the Editor you want to use local
TAed                    <- name of the online editor
s:startcsh              <- script for the Shell if you want to start
                           some minor things with the shell

@endnode

@node commandsfile "The commandsfile"
The SMS_#.cmds commandsfile

; Command file for SMS
; 15 entries 
; NOTE: change like the normal config in TA, but don't add extra lines !!!
; Now come the menu entries, use the key provided to help you
; ********************** ***
N edit news...           200
U userlist...            200
R rescan messagebase...  200
L read logfiles...       200
E ed user(s)...          200
$ shell...               200
V validate user(s)...    200
B Ban/Unban user(s)...   200
D delete user...         200
C view config...         200
# update filelist...     200
+ config SMS...          255
M show flags             200
Q quit...                200
F fumigate user(s)...    200
; *** This Line must be the last ! no RETURN (CR) after this ! ***

In the above example, the installed privilege access level is 200. 
So all you CoSysop can do anything in SMS but not editing the config !

NOTE: It's necessary that the last line is the comment in the config !
      Return after this line may not exist !

If you think, that one commandsfile for all lines are enough, {"contact" link freeware} me on
my various adresses !

@endnode

