@node options "Commands of SysopMenu"

These commands are available yet...

 @{" Quit                   " link quititno} - simple quit the SysopMenu 
 @{" Edit News              " link newsedit} - edit the Newsfile
 @{" List users             " link userlist} - list users
 @{" Read Log               " link logreadq} - read the logs
 @{" Edit user              " link useredit} - edit a specified user
 @{" Shell                  " link shelloni} - enter the Dosshell
 @{" Ban user Menu          " link banauser} - enter the user ban menu
 @{" Validate New user(s)   " link validate} - validate new users
 @{" Delete user(s)         " link deleteit} - delete a user
 @{" Configuration Summary  " link lookconf} - look up BBS config
 @{" Update File List       " link updateli} - update the file list
 @{" Edit Sysop Menu Config " link editsyso} - edit the SysopM config
 @{" Meaning of Flags       " link showflag} - show the meaning of flags
 @{" Fumigate userlist      " link fumigate} - Fumigate the userlist

@endnode

@node quititno "Quit the SysopMenu :-("
Quit

Why do you wan't to quit this program ???

Ok, this option simple bring you back to BBS.

@endnode

@node newsedit "Edit the Newsfile"
Edit the Newsfile

Here you can edit the Newsfile.

If you are local, simply your favourit editor is used and load the Newsfile.

If you are online, the newsfile was reading by TAed !
Then simple edit it and save it as a normal mail.

Most the CoSys do this on this way. So tell him how to use it.

Note: The Editor didn't support ANSI at this time so do not user ANSI in your
      newsfile. commands like ctrl+L may not exist in the newsfile, because 
      Sami's Editor has some problems with it. So make an CLS before sending
      the newsfile and delete ctrl+L in your newsfile !

@endnode

@node userlist "Userlist"
Userlist

This is a great function for the Sysop to list the Users and BTW edit it.
You can show them, correct parameters (by editing them) and control all
your users ! The Cosysop can't see the passwords from the user and can't edit
it ! Editing himself and the Sysop is denied for him ! So don't worry when he
is using SMS :-)

@endnode

@node logreadq "Read log"
Read Log(s)

Here you can read all logs btw. all system activities.

NOTE: All logs must be in the same BBS:System dir at this time ! I'll work
      an an method to change this...

@endnode

@node useredit "User edit"
User edit

When you enter this, you will be prompted for a username.
If the user exists you can edit it. It's quiete simple.
Follow the screenmessages. 

Since v1.14 it's possible to enter the handle from a user to edit
him !

Note: The Cosys isn't able to edit the Sysop or himself !

@endnode

@node shelloni "Dos Shell"
Dosshell

Enter the Shell. 
It is simple a Shell uses FIFO and TrShell.

You can start a Script with the Shell. I write a C-Shell Startup batch so
I have the powerful C-Shell online.

@endnode

@node banauser "(Re)Ban user"
Ban user menu

Here you can ban a user,reban a user and view banned users.

@endnode

@node validate "Validate new user"
Validate new Users

Here you can check if new users joined the BBS and validate them.

@endnode

@node deleteit "Delete a user"
Delete a user

Delete a user.
You will be prompted for a username.
Then you will be asked, if you really wanted to delete the user.

Note: The CoSys can't delete the Sysop !

@endnode

@node lookconf "Configuration Summary"
Configuration Summary

Simple prompt the BBS Configuration and the online baudrate.

@endnode

@node updateli "Update Filelist"
Update File List

This option will check if new files lie in the files dir. If yes,
than you will be promted for a description.

NOTE: This is an external function of SMS and the script 'UpdF.rexx'
      can be used from the shell...

@endnode

@node editsyso "Edit Sysop Config Menu"
Edit Config

You can edit the Config from this menu.

NOTE: Make sure that you doesn't allow to use this funtion from your CoSys !
      Set the access of this option up to 255.

@endnode

@node showflag "Show Flags meaning"
Meaning of Flags

Show you an the CoSys the meaning of flags.
It's good for the CoSys (an online help) to work much better.

@endnode

@node fumigate "Fumigate userlist"
Fumigate userlist

Here you must enter a date to check if a user had called since this date.
If not, he will be marked and after that a prompt will be occure to delete this
users.

Since v2.01 a prompt occure to ask for each user to delete them. It's more
work to fumigate but more safety :-)

@endnode

@node history "History of TA-SMS"

Note: TA-SMS based on the SysopMenu I've written a few time ago.

V1.0  - First official release !

V1.05 - show the variable CONFIG and not SMS_#.cfg im SysopConfigEd
      - corrected bug in userlist (aborted program sometimes)
      - add a range function in File Area update
      - add fumigate userlist (makes TrMaint complete in this menu!)
      - make some little changes and make-up

V1.06 - added cursor keys in the logread-function so you can use the
        cursor keys to scroll the log
      - change all commands keys to the same as TrMaint, makes it more
        compatible
      - corrected some bugs in the News Edit

V1.12 - add DELETE User to Userlistmenu
      - Holger Scherer's tool FlagConvert is now intigrated
      - now Ansi Color from TA Config used !
      - something for the future - compatible to >v1.12b2 from TransAmiga
        ( read default language and protocol from userfile )
              
      - suggestion from Daniel Baumgartl (thanks that you said it, i'd never
        made this if you don't say i must work on .. :-) )
        now you can give each command your prefered command

        * ********************** *** 
        N edit news...           200
    
        ^ ^                      ^   
        | |                      access for command
        | displayed when executing
        pefered char fot the command

      - NOTE: changed the SMS_#.cfg so reinstall it !!
              now there is no sysopname,cosysname and dosaccess in the
        
V1.13 - change prompt in useredit (correction!)
      - now the userlist is read out from a Userlist.sms file ! fast up and
        sorted the users to their real number
      - CleanTaLog is no longer necessary, cause i program something to do this
        faster directly in my main-source 
        NOTE: only the CoSysops aren't allowed to see the passwd's in the logfile.
      - made a little check, that the access for the commands in the .cmds file are correct

V1.14 -internal version ! never released !

V2.0  -now it's possible to input the handle of a user to edit it
      -now it's multilanguage (it uses the language the user use in TA)
       the main config file has changed ! Line 4 and 5 immigrated to the
       language file                 
      -saving the config of SMS in the program itselfs create an bug - corrected !
      -removed the line Lines in the config. I don't know for what this line was :-)
       it could be that it was needed in further versions ...
      -corrected command strings in usered
      -correct bug - when you type an mark that doesn't exist SMS will be exit
      -correct bug - when a user use Userlist and edit users the normal edit user
       got an foreverloop (you can't exit edit user)
      -corrected bug (when a user enter the handle to edit, he can edit the sysop)
      -new command in Usered: H - Edit transfer protocol
      -new command in Usered added: edit ratio now edits byteratio, too
      -fileformats corrected to version 1.12g1 from TransAmiga
      -fast up fumigate user list a lot and changed the handling a little bit
      -change edit user routine ! more comfortable !
      -changed update userlist / removed sysopm.temp file
      -CreateUserlist now note the userdir of the actual line !

V2.01 -the editor was set to name TAed. some people renamed the name in TrEd so I
       decided to add the name to the config file. There you can change the name
       to your wishes
      -renamed 'ReBan' in 'UnBan' . No great work :-) but Sami means that this sounds
       better (He's the Boss :-) !)
      -complete rewritten of the program UpdF.rexx to v2.0 (now it works perfectly :-)!)
      -fumigate now asks for each user to delete them. 
       deleting the Sysop in this way is now impossible ! 

V2.02 -killed rescan part - sinve v1.12g2 it's not longer necessary
      -when deleting from userlist no update from Userlist.sms will
       be made - corrected
      -removed the path 'BBS:bin/' from the source so now it's necessary
       that there exists a path to your binary directory ! Thanx to John
       Kratz for this suggestion.

      
@endnode
